    "description": "XeroGraph is a Python package designed to evaluate data quality, categorize the nature of missingness, and guide imputation decisions in datasets with missing values. It facilitates data integrity by comparing the influence of various imputation methods on underlying distributions, providing a systematic framework for more accurate and transparent analyses.",
